msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Ecological-Niche-Modelling.en.adoc:171
msgid "Curves that deviate from normal distributions or are flat, may indicate that the variable may not be a good estimator of a species's fundamental nicehe.  However, some variables such as ice concentrations, the lower curve in the diagram above, do not work like that - very few species can live enclosed in ice!"
