#. type: Plain text
#: Use-Case-2.en.adoc:16
msgid "Mexico is a mega-diverse country with high numbers of species and high levels of endemism across all taxonomic groups.  The government is committed to assessing the conservation status of all its species and has agreed to develop a national red list applying IUCN Categories and Criteria to all vertebrate and invertebrate taxonomic groups by the year 2030.  As part of this process, they have started the assessment of arachnid groups and are now assessing the conservation status of all species within the family Theraposidae – the tarantulas."
